						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the <hi rend="italic">mukhamaṇḍapa</hi> of the Veṅkatēśvara svāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>MALAYA GAṆAPATI.</p>						

						<p>1250 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in the Śaka 1172, Māghamāsa Pūrnnami i.e. śu. 15, corresponding 1250 A.D. December 15, Saturday.</p>						

						<p>Badly damaged. Seems to register the gift of 50 cows <hi rend="italic">(mōdālu)</hi> probably to the god Vēngīśvara mahādēva by certain • • • Śriyādēvi, probably the queen of the Malaya Chief Gaṇapati.</p>						

						</summary>
